{"TIVER":[{"def":"A kind of ocher which is used in some parts of England in marking sheep.","pos":""}],"TIVOLI":[{"def":"A game resembling bagatelle, played on a special oblong board or table (Tivoli board or table), which has a curved upper end, a set of numbered compartments at the lower end, side alleys, and the surface studded with pins and sometimes furnished with numbered depressions or cups.","pos":""}],"TIVY":[{"def":"With great speed; -- a huntsman's word or sound.","pos":""}]}